      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROCKING ROMA (1) wasn't far away at the finish when 4th and beaten only 4.5 lengths (17.52) at Mandurah. Should be very hard to beat this time. WHERE'S THE LUCK (8) goes very well at this course having never missed the frame including three wins. Comes off a (17.43) win last time, scoring by 5.5 lengths in a Grade 5 over 300m at this track. Can feature in the finish. WEFFALEE SHIELD (2) has been in super consistent form, finishing in the minors at his last six runs. Last time finished 3rd over 400m at The Gardens beaten 6 lengths (23.02) behind Stylish Robbo in a Mix 1/2/3 on March 28. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Nicely placed to grab a well-deserved win. RIVERLAND SON (4) will be thereabouts while fresh.",
